Template: oscar-mcmaster/gui_loader
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Do you want to lauch the GUI interface to install?
 The OSCAR deb has a graphical interface installer for intalls from
 the desktop.  Say false to continue in console mode.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/upgrade
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Do you want to upgrade from the previous OSCAR version?
 OLD OSCAR INSTALL DETECTED. This option will remove your existing OSCAR program.
 It will not remove your existing data.
 .
 ***Do not run this option without a backup.***

Template: oscar-mcmaster/priorschema
Type: string
Default:
Description: What is the old schema name?

Template: oscar-mcmaster/billregion
Type: select
Choices: ON, BC, Other
Default: ON
Description: Which jurisdiction do you want configured?
 Select the jurisdiction that you want configureg.  Select BC if you live in British Columbia.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/phoneprefix
Type: string
Default:
Description: What is the telephone prefix for your local area ? (eg 905-, +49 89)

Template: oscar-mcmaster/triumvirate
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Have you installed or are you planning to install fax support from OSCAR?
 The OSCAR deb can set up the GUI to print signed output directly to Hylafax, if that is installed on your server.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/demo
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Do you want to install demo data?
 Demo data are offered for demonstration that can later be removed.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/password
Type: password
Default: 
Description: MySQL password:
 Please enter your MySQL password.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/eyeform
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you want to install the eyeform version?
 An optional version of Oscar is designed for Opthalmology.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/appt_intake_form
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Do you want to use the intake form?
 The intake form allows for users to add common vitals and other measurements from the schedule.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/NEW_CONTACTS_UI 
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Do you want to use the new contacts interface?
  The new contacts interface allows for an expanded number of relations and other contacts related to the patient.

Template: oscar-mcmaster/readme
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Do you want to read the README?
 The Readme file will give final installation and configuration instructions.  Type q to quit the Readme.